This paper deals with techniques for estimating the size of views in OLAP (Online Analytical Processing) systems, which are used for data warehousing and business intelligence. The paper discusses various statistical and probabilistic methods for view size estimation and compares them experimentally. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DB (Databases), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper also discusses machine learning techniques (such as multifractal statistical models) and probabilistic counting, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
